What you need to know:

KKRU development coordinator Ronald Okoth said Kenyan rugby players usually have an average of two years playing time when they attain 18, which puts them at a disadvantage in the global arenaHe pointed out that although Shujaa 7s team performs well, Kenya fails in 15s since senior players don't have enough exposure due to late introduction into the gameThe pilot project targets 20 select counties by taking advantage of the new Competency-based Curriculum where learners will play inter-counties, regional and national games